# ITCP239 React Native App - Project Roadmap

## 1) Project Goal
Build a production-like mobile e-commerce/service app using React Native (Expo) + Node/Express backend that satisfies all rubric items:
- CRUD with image upload/camera
- User auth + social login
- Review/ratings with purchase verification
- Cart persistence (SQLite preferred for full points)
- Transactions + push notifications + deep link to order details
- Search/filter
- Redux for order/product/review
- Drawer-based UI
- JWT and push-token backend handling

## 2) Confirmed Tech Stack
Frontend:
- Expo React Native + Expo Router
- Redux Toolkit + React Redux
- expo-camera, expo-image-picker
- expo-sqlite, expo-secure-store
- expo-notifications
- @react-navigation/drawer

Backend:
- Express + Mongoose + MongoDB
- JWT + bcryptjs
- Multer + Cloudinary
- Firebase Admin (social token verification)
- expo-server-sdk (push notification sender)
- express-validator

## 3) Milestone Plan (Execution Order)

### Milestone 0: Foundation Setup (Day 1)
Deliverables:
- Environment variables for backend, Cloudinary, Firebase, JWT, Expo push.
- Base folder/module structure finalized.
- API client setup in frontend with auth interceptor.

Tasks:
- Create `.env` schema and validation.
- Configure DB connection and app startup checks.
- Define shared response format and error middleware.

Acceptance criteria:
- Backend boots cleanly.
- Frontend can hit health-check endpoint.
- Basic logging and error responses are consistent.

---

### Milestone 1: User Auth + Profile (MP2 core + Unit 2 partial) (Days 2-3)
Deliverables:
- Register, login, token refresh/logout (if implemented), profile fetch/update.
- Profile avatar upload via camera/gallery.
- JWT stored in Expo SecureStore.

Tasks:
- Backend: `User` model, auth routes, bcrypt hashing, JWT issue/verify middleware.
- Frontend: auth screens, protected routes, SecureStore token persistence.
- Add push token field on user model (`pushTokens[]` recommended).

Acceptance criteria:
- User can register/login/logout.
- App remains logged in after app restart.
- User can update profile and avatar.
- JWT auth protects private endpoints.

---

### Milestone 2: Product/Service CRUD + Image Upload (MP1) (Days 4-5)
Deliverables:
- Product/service create/read/update/delete.
- Photo upload from camera or gallery.

Tasks:
- Backend: `Product` model, CRUD routes, multer + cloudinary upload.
- Frontend: admin/manage product screens and image capture/picker.
- Add list/detail views for browsing products.

Acceptance criteria:
- CRUD endpoints pass manual tests.
- Uploaded image URLs are persisted and displayed in app.
- Validation prevents invalid price/category payloads.

---

### Milestone 3: Search + Filters (Quiz 1) (Day 6)
Deliverables:
- Search by keyword.
- Filter by category and price range (target full points).

Tasks:
- Backend query parameters: `q`, `category`, `minPrice`, `maxPrice`.
- Frontend search bar + filter modal/panel + pagination optional.

Acceptance criteria:
- Combined filters return correct narrowed results.
- Empty/no-result states handled cleanly.

---

### Milestone 4: Reviews & Ratings with Purchase Verification (MP3 + Redux part) (Days 7-8)
Deliverables:
- Authenticated users can create/update their own reviews.
- Reviews only allowed for verified purchased products/services.

Tasks:
- Backend models: `Review`, relationship to `Order` and `User`.
- Rule enforcement middleware/service: purchased-and-completed check.
- Frontend UI for create/edit review from order history.
- Redux slice for review state/actions.

Acceptance criteria:
- Non-buyers cannot review.
- Buyer can edit only their own review.
- Product details show aggregate rating and review list.

---

### Milestone 5: Cart Persistence with SQLite (MP4 full points) (Day 9)
Deliverables:
- Cart saved locally in SQLite before checkout.
- Cart auto-restored on app launch.
- Cart cleared after successful checkout.

Tasks:
- Define SQLite cart table schema.
- Sync Redux cart state <-> SQLite operations.
- Add fallback recovery if DB read fails.

Acceptance criteria:
- Force-close/reopen app restores cart.
- Checkout success removes local cart entries.

---

### Milestone 6: Transactions + Status + Push Notifications (Term Test + Quiz 2) (Days 10-11)
Deliverables:
- Create completed transaction flow.
- Update transaction status (admin/staff role).
- Push notification sent on status update and promotions.
- Tapping notification opens order detail screen.

Tasks:
- Backend: `Order` model and status lifecycle.
- Save Expo push tokens on login; remove stale/invalid tokens.
- Use `expo-server-sdk` to send transactional and promo pushes.
- Frontend notification handlers + deep linking to order detail route.

Acceptance criteria:
- Status update triggers push.
- Tapping push routes user to correct order details page.
- Invalid push tokens are handled and cleaned up.

---

### Milestone 7: Redux Completion (Quiz 3) (Day 12)
Deliverables:
- Redux fully applied to product, order, and review flows.

Tasks:
- Create/normalize slices: `productSlice`, `orderSlice`, `reviewSlice`.
- Add loading/error states and thunk-based async calls.
- Ensure UI reads from Redux store, not scattered local states.

Acceptance criteria:
- Core data flows are centralized in Redux.
- Clear async lifecycle state handling in UI.

---

### Milestone 8: Drawer UI + Final UX Pass (Unit 1 + Term Test Lec) (Day 13)
Deliverables:
- Drawer-based navigation structure.
- Final UI polish and consistency pass.

Tasks:
- Add drawer routes for Home, Shop, Cart, Orders, Profile, Admin.
- Improve loading, empty states, validation and toasts.
- Ensure responsive behavior on common screen sizes.

Acceptance criteria:
- Drawer navigation works across protected/unprotected routes.
- UI is consistent and presentation-ready.

---

### Milestone 9: Integration Testing + Demo Readiness (Day 14)
Deliverables:
- End-to-end tested demo script.
- Backup demo data and known-issues list.

Tasks:
- Test matrix: auth, CRUD, reviews, cart restore, checkout, notifications.
- Seed script or manual seed data.
- Prepare presentation flow and contingency notes.

Acceptance criteria:
- All rubric items demonstrable in a single walkthrough.
- No blocker bugs for graded features.

---

## 4) Tools Reference

### Backend Tools

| Package | Purpose in this project |
|---|---|
| `express` | HTTP server — all API routes |
| `mongoose` | MongoDB ODM — User, Product, Order, Review models |
| `cors` | Allow frontend to call backend API |
| `dotenv` | Load `.env` vars (DB URL, JWT secret, Cloudinary keys, etc.) |
| `jsonwebtoken` | Issue and verify JWTs on login/register |
| `bcryptjs` | Hash user passwords before saving to DB |
| `multer` | Parse `multipart/form-data` image uploads |
| `multer-storage-cloudinary` | Stream multer uploads directly to Cloudinary |
| `cloudinary` | Store and serve product/avatar images |
| `firebase-admin` | Verify Google/Facebook ID tokens from Firebase on the server |
| `expo-server-sdk` | Send push notifications to Expo devices (order status + promos) |
| `express-validator` | Validate request body on auth/CRUD/review endpoints |
| `nodemon` (dev) | Auto-restart backend on file change during development |

### Frontend Tools

| Package | Purpose in this project |
|---|---|
| `expo-secure-store` | Store JWT token securely on device (Unit 2) |
| `expo-sqlite` | Persist cart contents locally; restore on app open (MP4 — 20pts) |
| `expo-notifications` | Receive push notifications; handle tap → order detail (Quiz 2 + Term Test) |
| `expo-camera` | Take product/avatar photos with device camera (MP1, MP2) |
| `expo-image-picker` | Pick photos from gallery for product/avatar upload (MP1, MP2) |
| `@reduxjs/toolkit` | Define `productSlice`, `orderSlice`, `reviewSlice` (Quiz 3) |
| `react-redux` | Connect Redux store to components |
| `axios` | API calls to backend; attach JWT in request interceptor |
| `expo-router` | File-based routing; deep link from notification to `/orders/[id]` |
| `expo-linking` | Handle deep links from push notification tap |
| `@react-navigation/native` | Navigation foundation |
| `@react-navigation/drawer` | Drawer navigation layout (Unit 1 — 20pts) ⚠️ Install required |
| `react-native-gesture-handler` | Required peer dep for drawer/navigation |
| `react-native-reanimated` | Animations for drawer and transitions |
| `react-native-safe-area-context` | Safe area for notch/drawer layouts |
| `react-native-screens` | Native screen optimization for navigation |
| `firebase` | Google/Facebook sign-in flow from app (MP2 — 20pts) |
| `expo-auth-session` | Manages the Google/Facebook OAuth redirect session ⚠️ Install required |
| `expo-web-browser` | Opens OAuth browser popup for Google/Facebook login ⚠️ Install required |
| `expo-crypto` | Generates PKCE code verifier for `expo-auth-session` ⚠️ Install required |
| `expo-constants` | Access `projectId` for Expo push token registration |
| `@react-native-async-storage/async-storage` | Peer dep for drawer + async storage fallback ⚠️ Install required |
| `expo-font` | Load custom fonts on startup |
| `expo-splash-screen` | Control splash screen until fonts/auth state loads |
| `expo-linear-gradient` | Gradient backgrounds (splash, banners) |
| `@expo/vector-icons` | Icons across UI (drawer, nav, buttons) |
| `phosphor-react-native` | Additional icon library |

### Missing Frontend Packages — Install Command

```bash
npx expo install @react-navigation/drawer @react-native-async-storage/async-storage expo-auth-session expo-web-browser expo-crypto
```

